  "prompt": "Can you have sex, have a period, and still be pregnant?",
  "response": "Let's address each part of your question:\n\n1. **Having Sex While Pregnant:**\n   Yes, you can have sex while pregnant. It is generally safe for most women, though some may need to take precautions or avoid it altogether based on their specific medical situation. It's always a good idea to consult with your healthcare provider to ensure it's safe for your particular pregnancy.\n\n2. **Having a Period While Pregnant:**\n   No, you do not have a period while pregnant. When you become pregnant, your body stops ovulating and menstruating. What some women may mistake for a period could be implantation bleeding, which is lighter and occurs when the fertilized egg attaches to the uterine lining. However, any bleeding during pregnancy should be discussed with a healthcare provider.\n\n3. **Being Pregnant:**\n   If you are pregnant, you will not have a menstrual period, but you can still have sex (unless advised otherwise by your healthcare provider).\n\nIn summary, you can have sex while pregnant, but you will not have a period during pregnancy. If you experience any bleeding, it's important to consult your healthcare provider to ensure everything is okay with your pregnancy.",
